ar%20case%20of%20employees%20disrupting%20and%20occupying%20work%20spaces%2C%20and%20making%20other%20employees%20feel%20threatened%20and%20unsafe%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20carefully%20confirmed%20and%20reconfirmed%20that%20every%20single%20person%20whose%20employment%20was%20terminated%20was%20directly%20and%20definitively%20involved%20in%20disruption%20inside%20our%20buildings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20the%20NLRB%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20said%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-memo-warning-employees-think-again-before-sit-in-protests-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einternal%20memo%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20April%2017%20that%20the%20protesters%20had%20taken%20over%20office%20spaces%20and%20defaced%20company%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBehavior%20like%20this%20has%20no%20place%20in%20our%20workplace%20and%20we%20will%20not%20tolerate%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20workers%20had%20voiced%20their%20dissent%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproject-nimbus-google-sundar-pichai-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProject%20Nimbus%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Google's%20%241.2%20billion%20joint%20contract%20with%20Amazon%20to%20provide%20artificial%20intelligence%20and%20cloud%20computing%20services%20to%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProtesters%20claimed%20that%20the%20contract%20%E2%80%94%20the%20details%20of%20which%20became%20public%20in%202021%20%E2%80%94%20would%20allow%20the%20Israeli%20government%20to%20surveil%20and%20displace%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Google%20told%20BI%20last%20month%20that%20the%20company's%20work%20was%20not%20directed%20at%20highly%20sensitive%20or%20classified%20military%20projects%20relevant%20to%20weapons%20or%20intelligence%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20been%20very%20clear%20that%20the%20Nimbus%20contract%20is%20for%20workloads%20running%20on%20our%20commercial%20cloud%20by%20Israeli%20government%20ministries%2C%20who%20agree%20to%20comply%20with%20our%20Terms%20of%20Service%20and%20Acceptable%20Use%20Policy%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Google%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ongoing%20dispute%20between%20Google%20and%20some%20of%20its%20employees%20highlights%20companies'%20tricky%20balance%20between%20their%20business%20interests%20and%20their%20workers'%20desire%20for%20self-expression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2023%2F12%2F02%2Famazon-israel-gaza-war%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20around%201%2C700%20Amazon%20employees%20had%20signed%20a%20petition%20against%20Project%20Nimbus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESignatories%20argued%20that%20Amazon's%20cloud%20technology%20was%20going%20to%20be%20used%20by%20the%20Israelis%20to%20%26quot%3Brepress%20Palestinian%20activists%20and%20impose%20a%20brutal%20siege%20on%20Gaza.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20the%20petition%2C%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20Rob%20Munoz%20told%20The%20Post%20that%20the%20tech%20giant%20%26quot%3Bis%20focused%20on%20making%20the%20benefits%20of%20our%20world-leading%20cloud%20technology%20available%20to%20all%20our%20customers%2C%20wherever%20they%20are%20located.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-workers-fired-israel-contract-protests-file-complaint-nlrb-l2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714540725000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6631b5160dfb1341e901055b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-workers-fired-israel-contract-protests-f