D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheharrispoll.com%2Fbriefs%2Finflation-and-saving%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20Americans%20are%20saving%20regularly%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20majority%20of%20people%20are%20leaving%20money%20on%20the%20table%20by%20not%20taking%20advantage%20of%20this%20high-interest%20rate%20environment.%20Just%20having%20some%20savings%20in%20the%20bank%20isn't%20enough%2C%20and%20it%20doesn't%20always%20mean%20you're%20earning%20the%20APY%20you%20should.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20four%20reasons%20your%20savings%20aren't%20growing%20as%20much%20as%20you%20thought%2C%20and%20what%20you%20can%20do%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20You%20aren't%20keeping%20savings%20separate%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20savings%20should%20be%20in%20a%20separate%20account%20from%20the%20money%20you%20use%20for%20everyday%20spending%20%E2%80%94%20a%20savings%20account%2C%20not%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-checking-accounts%5C%22%3Echecking%20account%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20you%20have%20all%20of%20your%20income%20in%20one%20account%2C%20it's%20more%20difficult%20to%20determine%20what%20to%20spend%20and%20what%20not%20to%2C%20and%20to%20keep%20track%20of%20what%20is%20actually%20being%20saved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeeping%20your%20savings%20in%20a%20separate%20account%20leaves%20it%20untouched%20and%20allows%20it%20to%20grow.%20Even%20better%3A%20Set%20up%20automatic%20deductions%20from%20your%20paycheck%20into%20your%20savings%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20actually%20have%20a%20savings%20account%20with%20a%20separate%20bank%20and%20I%20do%20not%20have%20a%20debit%20card%20for%20it.%20That%20way%2C%20I%20keep%20myself%20from%20using%20those%20funds%20unless%20it%20is%20absolutely%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EToday's%20Featured%20Savings%20Accounts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ctable%20border%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Ctbody%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%3EAccount%20Name%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3EAPY%20(Annual%20Percentage%20Yield)%20Accurate%20as%20of%204%2F30%2F2024%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3EMinimum%20Account%20Opening%20Balance%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwestern-alliance-savings-account%5C%22%3EWestern%20Alliance%20Bank%20High-Yield%20Savings%20Premier%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E5.36%25%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E%24500%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fraisin-review%5C%22%3ENexBank%20High%20Yield%20Savings%20Account%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E5.26%25%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E%241%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%3EEverBank%20Performance%E2%84%A0%20Savings%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E5.15%25%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E%240%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%3ECIT%20Bank%20Platinum%20Savings%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E5.05%25%20(with%20%245%2C000%20minimum%20balance)%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E%24100%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%3EWealthfront%20Cash%20Account%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E5.00%25%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E%241%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%3EBarclays%20Online%20Savings%20Account%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E4.35%25%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E%240%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftbody%3E%3C%2Ftable%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20You're%20still%20using%20a%20traditional%20savings%20account%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETraditional%20savings%20accounts%20are%20certainly%20one%20way%20to%20save%20your%20money%2C%20but%20they're%20not%20ideal%2C%20especially%20now.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-savings-account-interest-rate%5C%22%3Eaverage%20savings%20account%20interest%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20is%200.46%25%20APY%2C%20but%20high-yield%20savings%20accounts%20are%20paying%20much%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Ehigh-yield%20savings%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20paying%20more%20than%205%25%20APY%20right%20now.%20With%20a%20higher%20annual%20percentage%20yield%2C%20your%20money%20can%20make%20more%20money%20just%20sitting%20in%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20You%20aren't%20meeting%20the%20requirements%20for%20the%20highest%20APY%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECheck%20with%20your%20bank%20and%20read%20the%20fine%20print%20for%20the%20specific%20requirements%20to%20get%20the%20highest%20APY%20available.%20For%20example%2C%20you%20may%20need%20to%20maintain%20a%20minimum%20balance%20or%20set%20up%20direct%20deposits%20to%20receive%20the%20highest%20APY%20advertised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20banks%20may%20have%20a%20new%20customer%20restriction%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20that%20if%20you%20learn%20that%20your%20bank%20is%20offering%20a%20higher%20APY%2C%20it%20may%20only%20be%20for%20new%20customers%2C%20and%20that%20new%2C%20higher%20rate%20isn't%20available%20to%20you.%20If%20that's%20the%20case%2C%20don't%20panic%3A%20You're%20allowed%20to%20open%20multiple%20accounts%20at%20different%20banks%20and%20get%20a%20better%20rate%20on%20your%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20You%20aren't%20saving%20regularly%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20you%20save%2C%20the%20more%20money%20you%20have%20to%20grow.%20No%20matter%20how%20high%20the%20interest%20rate%2C%20it%20is%20applied%20to%20the%20balance%20that%20is%20in%20the%20account.%20So%20the%20more%20you%20save%2C%20the%20more%20you%20can%20potentially%20earn%20due%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-compound-interest%5C%22%3Ecompound%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20increased%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFind%20ways%20to%20increase%20the%20amount%20you%20are%20saving.%20Don't%20think%20that%20you%20have%20to%20do%20it%20all%20at%20once.%20You%20can%20increase%20the%20amount%20steadily%20over%20time.%20The%20key%20to%20saving%20successfully%20is%20consistency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20started%20saving%2C%20I%20had%20%2450%20each%20pay%20period%20automatical